The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed ten new cases of coronavirus in the country. This was disclosed via a tweet on their verified Twitter page. The new cases were recorded in Lagos and Abuja. The tweet reads, “Ten new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria; 7 in Lagos and 3 in the FCT. “As at 08:00 pm 2nd April there are 184 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria. Twenty have been discharged with two deaths “As at 08:00 pm 2nd April, there are 184 confirmed cases, 20 discharged, 2 deaths.”